clinical_particulars.therapeutic_indications: Peginesatide is used for the treatment of anemia due to chronic kidney disease CKD in adult patients on dialysis

contraindications.disease: The most common adverse events 10 are dyspnea diarrhea nausea cough and arteriovenous fistula site complication
contraindications.pharmacodynamics: Peginesatide increases the reticulocyte count and levels of hemoglobin It also increases RBC count hematocrit and soluble transferrin receptor protein in a dose dependent manner
